Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.02,0:00:08.94,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,So hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.94,0:00:12.02,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,It's getting hotter by the day...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.02,0:00:14.39,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,They say summer this year will be hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.39,0:00:16.92,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry we only come by to cool down.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.92,0:00:19.49,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I know you don't handle heat \Nwell due to your natures.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.49,0:00:22.54,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! We don't need \Nto be shy, Yukki!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.54,0:00:23.81,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,That's kinda annoying, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.81,0:00:27.32,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,This year is particularly hot, \Nand not just for these two.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.32,0:00:28.42,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.42,0:00:30.94,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,With the height of summer coming up,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.94,0:00:34.01,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,we should consider what demis, \Nparticularly Hikari and Yuki,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.01,0:00:35.39,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,can do to get by.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.39,0:00:36.58,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,That's a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.58,0:00:39.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every year, I worry about how \NI should spend the summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.61,0:00:42.73,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,As it is, it's already pretty rough \Non you and Hikari-chan, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.73,0:00:45.48,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei, that's great! \NLet's do it! Right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.48,0:00:46.72,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Not right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.72,0:00:48.49,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.49,0:00:49.86,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,It's already late.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.13,0:00:52.75,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I want to think \Nit over myself first.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.75,0:00:53.76,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.76,0:00:55.19,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.19,0:00:56.66,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,How about Saturday?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.66,0:00:59.29,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have plenty of time on Saturday.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.29,0:01:01.04,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.74,0:01:04.83,Office,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs18\fad(1363,1)}How Vampires and Snow Women \NCan Spend Summer in Comfort
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.43,0:01:23.02,ShowTitle,Title,0000,0000,0000,,Interviews with Monster Girls
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.01,0:02:43.55,Title1,Title,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(480,517)}Demi-chans Want to Support
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.76,0:02:43.07,Default,Ohkawa,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Tetsu-sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.07,0:02:44.26,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect timing!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.55,0:02:47.44,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,We're playing soccer after school, \Nbut we're short on players.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.44,0:02:49.03,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,Will you be our goalie?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.03,0:02:50.37,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,No, I won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.37,0:02:52.50,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,Why not? You have nothing \Nelse to do, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.50,0:02:55.02,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,What, exactly, do you think teachers are?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.42,0:02:57.71,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, I can't today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.71,0:03:01.62,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I'm working on a plan to help Yuki and \NHikari pass the summer in comfort.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.62,0:03:03.12,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,What? Again?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.44,0:03:04.00,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.00,0:03:06.63,Default,Ohkawa,0000,0000,0000,,You've become the demi-chans' \Npersonal teacher, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.63,0:03:08.40,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? H-Have I?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.40,0:03:09.81,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you have!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.81,0:03:13.54,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,You're the only one they'll \Ntalk to about their bodies!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.21,0:03:15.49,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.49,0:03:16.50,Default,Head,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.46,0:03:19.26,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Vice Principal...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.64,0:03:20.56,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.56,0:03:26.26,Default,Head,0000,0000,0000,,Offering counsel to our demi-human \Nstudents is a very good thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.26,0:03:30.37,Default,Head,0000,0000,0000,,But working too hard at it \Ncauses a bit of a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.37,0:03:34.48,Default,Head,0000,0000,0000,,You need to pay attention to students \Nwho aren't demi-humans, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.48,0:03:35.81,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.37,0:03:40.68,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, I think Tetsu-sensei looks after \Nnon-demi students really well!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.03,0:03:42.56,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, s-sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.56,0:03:47.56,Default,Head,0000,0000,0000,,Then why do the demi-human students \Nonly rely on Takahashi-sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.78,0:03:48.83,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.83,0:03:50.01,Default,Ohkawa,0000,0000,0000,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.79,0:03:52.77,Default,Head,0000,0000,0000,,You're trying too hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.46,0:03:56.48,Default,Head,0000,0000,0000,,If you would show some restraint,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.48,0:03:59.55,Default,Head,0000,0000,0000,,the demi-humans' dependence on \Nyou would disperse naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.87,0:04:00.95,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,But I—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.95,0:04:03.07,Default,Head,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think those students
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.07,0:04:07.01,Default,Head,0000,0000,0000,,having no one but you to \Nrely on is a good thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.70,0:04:12.60,Default,Head,0000,0000,0000,,It may take time, but rather \Nthan depend on you alone,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.02,0:04:16.36,Office,Head,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs18}How Vampires and Snow Women \NCan Spend Summer in Comfort \N\N{\fs16}Takahashi Tetsuo
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.60,0:04:16.36,Default,Head,0000,0000,0000,,they can resolve their problems by \Ninteracting with other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.66,0:04:18.86,Default,Head,0000,0000,0000,,Would that not be a more natural course?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.97,0:04:25.22,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,That... may be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.34,0:04:30.57,Default,Ohkawa,0000,0000,0000,,But I do see the vice principal's point.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.57,0:04:31.60,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.60,0:04:34.08,Default,Ohkawa,0000,0000,0000,,Tetsu-sensei isn't the only \Nteacher in the school.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.08,0:04:36.79,Default,Ohkawa,0000,0000,0000,,If they could turn to lots of \Npeople, wouldn't it be better?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.79,0:04:39.59,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,Would it turn out that way if \NTetsu-sensei stopped trying?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.59,0:04:40.74,Default,Ohkawa,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.74,0:04:42.17,Default,Ohkawa,0000,0000,0000,,The vice principal said as much.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.70,0:04:44.24,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,Satake-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.24,0:04:46.27,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,Please, Satake...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.27,0:04:48.17,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,Satake-kyun!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.79,0:04:51.92,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,If he stopped, would they \Nturn to me instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.92,0:04:54.44,Default,Ohkawa,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I don't know if they'd \Nspecifically turn to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.54,0:04:59.23,Default,Kimura,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.68,0:05:01.73,Default,Kimura,0000,0000,0000,,I was trying to pass it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.73,0:05:03.72,Default,Kimura,0000,0000,0000,,He said that, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.72,0:05:06.44,Default,Kimura,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, they've never \Nasked me for help, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.44,0:05:07.68,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.68,0:05:09.83,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,You'd probably be a last resort.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.83,0:05:10.50,Default,Kimura,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.50,0:05:12.27,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.27,0:05:17.01,Default,Ohkawa,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I wonder what the \Ndemi-chans need advice about.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.01,0:05:20.96,Default,Ohkawa,0000,0000,0000,,Demi-humans are no different than \Nregular humans, are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.96,0:05:24.39,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,Kusakabe and Takanashi were saying \Nthey don't handle heat well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.39,0:05:26.97,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,He was wondering how they can \Nlive in "comfort" for summer
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.97,0:05:30.08,Default,Kimura,0000,0000,0000,,They really have to rely on Takahashi \Nfor every little thing like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.08,0:05:31.81,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm... Maybe that's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.74,0:05:35.28,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,Takanashi drinks a lot of tomato juice,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.28,0:05:37.67,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,so maybe you could ask her \Nwhich brand is best.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.67,0:05:39.35,Default,Kimura,0000,0000,0000,,Look it up online.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.35,0:05:41.24,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,Like online reviews are worth anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.24,0:05:41.90,Default,Kimura,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.84,0:05:44.57,Default,Imori,0000,0000,0000,,You know...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.49,0:05:47.86,Default,Imori,0000,0000,0000,,Should we really think of demis
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.86,0:05:50.54,Default,Imori,0000,0000,0000,,as human, just like the rest of us?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.54,0:05:51.12,Default,Ohkawa,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.12,0:05:53.03,Default,Kimura,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, that's a little...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.03,0:05:54.75,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying they aren't?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.75,0:05:56.29,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,That's discrimination!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.29,0:05:57.57,Default,Imori,0000,0000,0000,,Is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.57,0:06:01.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Earlier, you said they're basically \Nthe same as regular humans,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.89,0:06:05.30,Default,Imori,0000,0000,0000,,but that means something about \Nthem is different, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.26,0:06:09.06,Default,Imori,0000,0000,0000,,To ignore that and treat them \Nas normal humans...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.06,0:06:12.05,Default,Imori,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't that be real discrimination?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.50,0:06:13.89,Default,Imori,0000,0000,0000,,I think Takahashi
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.89,0:06:17.92,Default,Imori,0000,0000,0000,,understands them very well, \Nincluding those parts of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.40,0:06:21.69,Default,Imori,0000,0000,0000,,That's probably why they find \Nhim so easy to confide in.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.06,0:06:24.41,Default,Imori,0000,0000,0000,,And what about us?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.41,0:06:27.52,Default,Imori,0000,0000,0000,,Would a demi want to seek \Nadvice from someone
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.52,0:06:30.49,Default,Imori,0000,0000,0000,,who just blindly thinks of \Nthem as normal humans?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.82,0:06:33.62,Default,Imori,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't that scare them? \NAnd take courage?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.34,0:06:36.65,Default,Imori,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe they want to be more at ease,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.65,0:06:39.29,Default,Imori,0000,0000,0000,,asking for help or talking \Nabout demi-human stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.86,0:06:44.67,Default,Imori,0000,0000,0000,,I guess we don't really know \Nanything about them at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.62,0:06:49.27,Default,Imori,0000,0000,0000,,At least, that's what I was thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.20,0:06:52.23,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.89,0:06:54.60,Default,Ohkawa,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, does that mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.60,0:06:57.99,Default,Kimura,0000,0000,0000,,The reason the demi-chans \Nonly talk to Takahashi...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.99,0:07:00.94,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,...isn't because Tetsu-sensei \Ntries too hard. But because...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.39,0:07:04.55,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,Actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.96,0:07:07.88,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,You've really thought this through, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.88,0:07:08.55,Default,Ohkawa,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.55,0:07:09.20,Default,Kimura,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.20,0:07:10.15,Default,Imori,0000,0000,0000,,I'll hit you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.92,0:07:15.05,Default,Imori,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I probably wouldn't have \Never considered all this
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.05,0:07:17.43,Default,Imori,0000,0000,0000,,if there weren't any demi-chans around.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.43,0:07:18.47,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.47,0:07:22.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometime, maybe we should ask \NTetsu-sensei about this stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.15,0:07:23.13,Default,Ohkawa,0000,0000,0000,,I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.44,0:07:26.58,Default,Ohkawa,0000,0000,0000,,But maybe he also worries about \Nweird, little things like these.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.58,0:07:27.80,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, it's fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.80,0:07:29.66,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,Tetsu-sensei's a dependable guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.66,0:07:30.97,Default,Kimura,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.97,0:07:34.60,Default,Kimura,0000,0000,0000,,I think being too dependable can \Nactually complicate things.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.89,0:07:37.89,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Trying too hard...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.89,0:07:38.27,Office,Text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs18}How Vampires and Snow Women \NCan Spend Summer in Comfort \N\N{\fs16}Takahashi Tetsuo
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.89,0:07:39.68,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.14,0:07:41.39,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Heya!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.98,0:07:43.44,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.65,0:07:46.62,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,Have you been thinking up a \Nplan for us to handle summer?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.62,0:07:48.40,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,May I hear it, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.72,0:07:52.15,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,A-Ah, yeah... I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.38,0:07:54.28,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.76,0:08:02.83,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.20,0:08:06.21,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Today... I've got... some things.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.97,0:08:19.97,Eyecatch,,0000,0000,0000,,Interviews with Monster Girls
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.96,0:08:23.38,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,What was wrong with Sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.38,0:08:25.39,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Did he suddenly have some work?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.39,0:08:28.21,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't seem that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.21,0:08:30.38,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Yukki?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.38,0:08:32.21,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,Including this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.21,0:08:35.30,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,I think we've gotten used to \Nhaving Takahashi-sensei
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.30,0:08:39.35,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,think about things for us and \Ndo all kinds of stuff for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.35,0:08:42.93,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,Rather, maybe we've come \Nto expect it of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.93,0:08:43.96,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.49,0:08:49.25,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,Like, maybe we've been taking \Nadvantage of his good will.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.52,0:08:52.26,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,You think we've become a burden to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.26,0:08:54.61,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, there's no way!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.61,0:08:57.09,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,A while back, I asked Sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.59,0:09:00.34,Default - flashback,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,After talking to you all these times,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.34,0:09:04.82,Default - flashback,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I've come to think some legends about \Nvampires are rooted in their traits,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.35,0:09:04.10,BlackWhite,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Originated from Traits \N— Sucking Blood \N— Dislike of Light \N— Aversion to Garlic
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.10,0:09:10.57,BlackWhite,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Originated from Religious Beliefs \N— Aversion to Crosses \N— No Reflection in Mirrors
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.82,0:09:09.46,Default - flashback,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,while others are religious concepts, \Ncreated by human fears.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.46,0:09:10.57,Default - flashback,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.57,0:09:13.69,Default - flashback,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,And what do we get by knowing that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.25,0:09:16.07,Default - flashback,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,It's fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.07,0:09:17.41,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,That's how he acted.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.70,0:09:20.23,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,Basically, he just wants to know?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.23,0:09:22.64,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Right, right. So everything is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.64,0:09:26.33,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Then why did he act like that earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.87,0:09:29.67,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe something happened \Nwith another teacher?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.13,0:09:33.84,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,If that were it, then we can't interfere.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.47,0:09:38.80,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,If we can't ask Sensei, we can ask Sakki!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.75,0:09:40.93,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be right back.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.38,0:09:42.58,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Hikari-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.58,0:09:45.06,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think that will help...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.23,0:09:49.15,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.62,0:09:53.12,Default,Head,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.12,0:09:54.49,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is Sakki—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.78,0:09:57.60,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, Satou-sensei here? \NI wanted to ask her something.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.60,0:10:01.21,Default,Head,0000,0000,0000,,I believe Satou-sensei is \Nworking in the schoolyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.21,0:10:04.13,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,She's in the schoolyard? Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.13,0:10:06.20,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be going, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.51,0:10:12.92,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,We have to think about how to get \Nalong with demi-chans, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.43,0:10:16.41,Default,Kimura,0000,0000,0000,,Well, each of us is different.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.41,0:10:19.37,Default,Kimura,0000,0000,0000,,And we have no problem talking \Nto one another about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.37,0:10:20.45,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,I get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.45,0:10:23.58,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,You look kinda mean, but you \Nsay some smart stuff—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.58,0:10:24.06,Default,Kimura,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.30,0:10:27.77,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,I mean... That's the kind of \Ndifference you meant, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.77,0:10:30.25,Default,Kimura,0000,0000,0000,,That was just you insulting me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.17,0:10:32.69,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.69,0:10:35.15,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey, what's the rush?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.15,0:10:36.87,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Have you seen Sakki?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.87,0:10:38.50,Default,Ohkawa,0000,0000,0000,,You mean Satou-sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.50,0:10:39.17,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.17,0:10:41.87,Default,Imori,0000,0000,0000,,She's pruning trees on the other \Nside of the athletic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.87,0:10:42.93,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.93,0:10:45.25,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Takanashi, hang on a sec.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.05,0:10:48.71,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, it's about Tetsu-sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.42,0:10:50.71,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.01,0:10:54.50,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,So that's what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.96,0:10:56.63,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.04,0:10:57.76,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.09,0:11:00.10,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I'll try to do something, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.10,0:11:01.72,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Satakke.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.10,0:11:04.51,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,"Satakke"?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.01,0:11:06.80,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.80,0:11:08.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds like some kind \Nof monster, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.90,0:11:09.99,Default,Ohkawa,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.70,0:11:12.90,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I did say I wanted a nickname, \Nbut come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.74,0:11:12.90,Default,Three,0000,0000,0000,,Lucky... He got a nickname.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.45,0:11:18.61,Default,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... So the vice principal said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.61,0:11:19.79,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.79,0:11:22.66,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Then, that's why Takahashi-sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.66,0:11:26.30,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we really were taking \Nadvantage of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.30,0:11:28.37,Default,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,No, that isn't true at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.73,0:11:30.83,Default,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,There are four demis at this school.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.83,0:11:35.42,Default,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,And I think we're truly blessed to \Nhave Takahashi-sensei here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.73,0:11:39.54,Default,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,We've all been saved many times \Nbecause of that fact, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.54,0:11:40.74,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,Well, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.74,0:11:42.19,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Lots of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.19,0:11:45.68,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,But the vice principal didn't \Nhave to say that to him...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.09,0:11:48.53,Default,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,The vice principal can be strict,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.53,0:11:50.95,Default,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,but he's an admirable man, \Nwith a passion for education.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.95,0:11:53.07,Default,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,What he said wasn't wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.07,0:11:56.94,Default,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,And I don't think he meant to shut \NTakahashi-sensei down completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.94,0:11:59.81,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,What can we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.81,0:12:02.80,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if I could just start \Ntalking to someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.80,0:12:04.61,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,And it would make them uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.98,0:12:08.12,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I've got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.33,0:12:12.97,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Let's make Sensei feel better!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.14,0:12:23.09,Default - flashback,Head,0000,0000,0000,,You're trying too hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.34,0:12:25.30,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I am...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.26,0:12:29.24,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,At first, I was just interested \Nin demi-humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.24,0:12:31.86,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I hate to admit it, but it was \Nmainly personal interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.86,0:12:36.14,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,But over time, I realized demi-chans \Nhave their own troubles.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.14,0:12:38.40,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,And I wanted to help them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.77,0:12:40.57,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I hoped I'd be able to support them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.86,0:12:44.11,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,But maybe it was unnecessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.44,0:12:47.92,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Those girls have a better handle \Non things than I realized.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.92,0:12:51.66,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I'd helped Yuki with her \Nconcern over her unique nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.40,0:12:56.00,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,But maybe I didn't need to do \Nanything about that, either...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.93,0:13:01.18,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Getting over it by herself probably \Nwould've made her stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.18,0:13:03.99,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,And if she needs to rely on \Nsomeone, she's better off
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.99,0:13:08.29,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,being able to confide in family, \Nclassmates, and many others.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.82,0:13:11.93,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Was I being too intrusive?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.59,0:13:16.02,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Souma tries to study demi-humans \Nfrom a researcher's perspective.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.02,0:13:21.53,SignA,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Inbox \N{\fs16}Sender: Souma \NRecipient: Takahashi Tetsuo \N\NHey, I tried sounding out my professor about \Nresearching Machi-kun, but he had a \Npretty glum look on his face. Ha ha ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.44,0:13:19.01,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, that benefits demi-humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.01,0:13:20.09,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,And it may even
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.09,0:13:23.49,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,be the key to learning something \Nthat could change the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.40,0:13:27.30,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,There's more than one way \Nto help demi-humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.30,0:13:29.08,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Instead of doing it as a teacher,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.08,0:13:32.62,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,maybe keeping some distance as a \Nresearcher could be an option.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.47,0:13:36.62,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, from Hikari...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.87,0:13:35.87,SignA,Text,0000,0000,0000,,Inbox \N{\fs16}Sender: Takanashi Hikari \NRecipient: Takahashi Tetsuo \N\NVideo Letter
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.14,0:13:40.18,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,So slow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.34,0:13:45.88,Default - italics,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, it's started!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.88,0:13:47.22,Default - italics,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Already?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.44,0:13:53.72,Default - italics,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, first, Yukki will express her \Nthanks to our troubled Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.72,0:13:56.24,Default - italics,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm not ready for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.80,0:13:58.55,Default - italics,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not ready for this...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.25,0:14:01.40,Default - italics,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm not ready—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.40,0:14:03.03,Default - italics,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, start!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.98,0:14:07.76,Default - italics,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,U-Um, Takahashi-sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.76,0:14:10.00,Default - italics,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,This is Yuki. Kusakabe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.00,0:14:12.24,Default - italics,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for all you've done.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.24,0:14:15.50,Default - italics,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I know you might be... well,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.50,0:14:20.35,Default - italics,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,worried you doted on us too much,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.35,0:14:22.77,Default - italics,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,or that you might have overreached.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.77,0:14:27.07,Default - italics,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,Like when I came to you for advice \Nabout my physical traits.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.53,0:14:32.16,Default - italics,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, like even if I hadn't, time would \Nhave solved the problem,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.16,0:14:35.30,Default - italics,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,and maybe that would \Nhave been better for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.30,0:14:38.11,Default - italics,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,I certainly can't deny that possibility...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.11,0:14:42.16,Default - italics,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, but I'm not saying I think \Nthat's what I should have done!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.16,0:14:47.01,Default - italics,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,I just mean that, in terms of possibility, \Nno possibility is really impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.01,0:14:49.26,Default - italics,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,What I mean is, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.26,0:14:54.10,Default - italics,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm very grateful for all the \Nadvice you've given me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.10,0:14:55.90,Default - italics,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,One thing I can say without doubt
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.90,0:15:00.69,Default - italics,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,is that, thanks to you, my concerns \Nover my constitution were resolved!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.69,0:15:03.98,Default - italics,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I got to eat popsicles \Nwith the others that day,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.98,0:15:07.27,Default - italics,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,which meant I could spend more \Ntime having fun with them!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.27,0:15:10.55,Default - italics,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,Um, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.72,0:15:14.71,Default - italics,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,My mind just went blank.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.71,0:15:16.42,Default - italics,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Macchi, you're next!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.60,0:15:25.06,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Takahashi-sensei, this is Machi.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.06,0:15:28.21,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Hello. How are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.21,0:15:31.18,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,It hasn't been very long since I met you,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.18,0:15:34.33,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,but it feels like it's been a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.33,0:15:38.70,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,And that's because you've done \Nso many things for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.70,0:15:40.52,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.52,0:15:43.30,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Thinking about it, you were always
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.30,0:15:46.32,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,eager to listen, from when we first met.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.32,0:15:53.00,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,It made me realize how nice talking freely \Nwith someone about dullahans is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.00,0:15:56.01,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,And you aren't only kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.01,0:16:00.72,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,You also scolded me when \NI acted out of line.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.72,0:16:05.29,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,You might say that's just \Nyour job as an educator.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.29,0:16:09.36,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,But if nothing else, in all my life so far,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.36,0:16:14.61,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,no other teacher has ever approached \Nme so directly as a dullahan!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.61,0:16:17.94,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you would be the same teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.94,0:16:22.61,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,toward any student, demi or otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.61,0:16:26.99,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you had no particular \Ninterest in demis,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.99,0:16:30.21,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure that if we three showed \Nup as new students,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.21,0:16:33.48,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,you would treat us the same \Nway you do now...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.40,0:16:40.81,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you'll continue to watch out for \Nus... no, for all kinds of students.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.81,0:16:43.78,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you'll advise us when \Nwe have problems,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.78,0:16:47.54,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,and scold us if we do something wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.54,0:16:50.64,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,I'll come see you in the biology \Nprep room again.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.64,0:16:52.47,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.36,0:16:55.57,Default - italics,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,Oops, I applauded without thinking!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.57,0:16:58.29,Default - italics,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Macchi, you're a good speaker! \NSuch an honor student!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.29,0:16:59.86,Default - italics,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.86,0:17:01.30,Default - italics,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, Sakki, you're next.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.30,0:17:02.74,Default - italics,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? I'm in this, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.19,0:17:03.62,Default - italics,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Go on, go on!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.74,0:17:05.18,Default - italics,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Yuki-chan! Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.18,0:17:07.94,Default - italics,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,I was trying to keep my voice \Nout of the recording...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.97,0:17:14.13,Default - italics,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, Takahashi-sensei, this is Satou. \NThanks for all your hard work.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.13,0:17:17.45,Default - italics,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,The girls are the stars here, \Nso I'll keep this simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.90,0:17:25.97,Default - italics,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,I rely on you a great deal, both as \Na teacher and as a succubus!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.97,0:17:30.86,Default - italics,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,I have endless respect for the way you \Nhandle everything with such sincerity!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.86,0:17:34.02,Default - italics,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for always helping me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.02,0:17:39.18,Default - italics,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,And I'll count on your continued \Nguidance and encouragement.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.72,0:17:42.68,Default - italics,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,Was that too formal?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.09,0:17:47.73,Default - italics,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,If anything ever bothers you,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.73,0:17:50.35,Default - italics,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,I'd be glad to listen as a colleague,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.35,0:17:54.67,Default - italics,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,even though I'm still a rookie, \Nso don't hesitate to talk to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.67,0:17:56.13,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll lend you my shoulder!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.13,0:18:00.74,Default - italics,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure some things aren't easy to \Ndiscuss in a normal setting, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.95,0:18:03.13,Default - italics,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.89,0:18:07.24,Default - italics,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we go for drinks sometime?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.61,0:18:10.80,Default - italics,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, just kidding...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.80,0:18:12.78,Default - italics,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,And that concludes our video letter!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.78,0:18:15.61,Default - italics,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? You aren't going \Nto talk, Hikari-chan?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.61,0:18:16.74,Default - italics,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,Hikari, no fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.74,0:18:17.86,Default - italics,Sakie,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.86,0:18:18.99,Default - italics,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,The end!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.76,0:18:30.21,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.97,0:18:32.84,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hikari?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.62,0:18:36.08,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.08,0:18:39.46,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Earlier, I sent you a video, \Nbut it was huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.46,0:18:43.26,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,So I wondered if you were able to \Nwatch it, and then I saw you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.26,0:18:44.56,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,From over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.56,0:18:45.77,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,From way over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.77,0:18:47.36,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.36,0:18:49.11,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,'Scuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.26,0:18:55.49,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.49,0:18:57.91,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.91,0:18:59.40,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I'll thank the others, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.40,0:19:01.16,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Satakke told me what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.16,0:19:03.60,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Satakke? Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.60,0:19:06.90,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,So I thought you might be down.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.90,0:19:08.25,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.61,0:19:11.84,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,But your video made me really happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.84,0:19:13.48,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I feel better now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.48,0:19:17.13,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,But I still think I might \Nhave gone too far.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.56,0:19:20.14,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,And maybe I should keep \Npace with everyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.14,0:19:21.51,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,No, not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.51,0:19:25.36,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,You can never take "trying" too far.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.36,0:19:29.48,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Saying a person who tried hard to move \Nforward "went too far" isn't right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.86,0:19:32.98,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,For one who's trying hard, \Npeople can support them,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.98,0:19:36.69,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,so their efforts are rewarded, \Nand show their gratitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.01,0:19:39.92,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,If they want to keep the same \Npace as that person,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.92,0:19:43.07,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,they need to try just as hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.78,0:19:48.60,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.05,0:19:53.57,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much for always \Ntrying so hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.57,0:19:57.62,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,When it comes to effort, I don't \Nwant to place second to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.62,0:20:06.60,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,So I'll also try hard, to repay all that \Nyou and everyone has done for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.40,0:20:14.15,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Ta-dah! That was your surprise \Nsecret video letter!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.42,0:20:24.69,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,There, there...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.69,0:20:25.53,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Stop that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.55,0:20:28.52,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,You're gonna make me cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.18,0:20:35.50,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Vice Principal!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.99,0:20:39.09,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to talk to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.09,0:20:41.31,Default,Head,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I wanted to talk to you, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.84,0:20:47.17,Default,Head,0000,0000,0000,,Before, I asked you to reconsider \Nyour contact with demi-humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.17,0:20:49.08,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, about that... I—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.08,0:20:50.77,Default,Head,0000,0000,0000,,Let's put that on hold.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.77,0:20:51.44,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.44,0:20:55.04,Default,Head,0000,0000,0000,,After lecturing you as I did, \Nforgive my saying this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.04,0:20:57.35,Default,Head,0000,0000,0000,,But I'd like you to continue demonstrating
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.35,0:21:00.21,Default,Head,0000,0000,0000,,the same competence you always have.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.21,0:21:01.32,Default,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.95,0:21:09.57,Default,Kimura,0000,0000,0000,,It's pretty heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.57,0:21:11.45,Default,Machi,0000,0000,0000,,When you're used to it, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.45,0:21:13.41,Default,Imori,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't know your skin was this cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.41,0:21:14.42,Default,Yuki,0000,0000,0000,,Surprised?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.42,0:21:16.12,Default,Imori,0000,0000,0000,,I bet summers really are tough for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.39,0:21:17.63,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,How about my arm?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.63,0:21:19.14,Default,Hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm... Four points!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.14,0:21:19.84,Default,Satake,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.41,0:21:24.82,Default,Head,0000,0000,0000,,As long as there are students who \Nare inspired by your actions,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.82,0:21:27.88,Default,Head,0000,0000,0000,,disavowing your efforts would be wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.81,0:21:41.15,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,The new life I stepped into this \Nspring with the demi-chans
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.15,0:21:43.40,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,was one of stimulation and excitement.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.97,0:21:48.87,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,How demis live their lives, what they think,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.87,0:21:54.23,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,how those who make contact with them \Nthink and how they change...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.00,0:21:57.21,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,I want to consider it all much, much more!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.25,0:22:01.96,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,At last,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.74,0:22:04.04,Default - italics,Tetsuo,0000,0000,0000,,summer is upon us!
